Our front page also told how War Minister John Profumo denied any "impropriety" in his relationship with model Christine Keeler. The following June he would be forced to quit after admitting he lied to Parliament about his affair with Keeler. 45 years ago (1977) Former President Richard Nixon recorded the first of a series of 12 interviews with journalist Sir David Frost about the Watergate scandal which led to his resignation in 1974. The 2008 film Frost/ Nixon, starring Michael Sheen, told the story behind the interviews. 39 years ago (1983) US President Ronald Reagan unveiled plans for the so-called Star Wars defence project using laser technology to intercept incoming nuclear missiles. Critics of the Strategic Defense Initiative claimed it would increase tension between the US and Russia and divert resources from domestic issues. The project was abandoned 10 years later. 